name: Father Figure Project: First Steps
description:
Chum Chum's first steps under the watchful eye of Guy Miller.

FOLLOW ME ON HERE:
Instagram | website | facebook | twitter | Google +


Speaking of "first steps", Spring/Summer 2014 is shaping up to be super-busy. The biggest news is that the book is definitely coming this fall! I'm happy that I found an amazing home for the first edition of the Father Figure book - www.ceibafoto.com. It's a brand-new imprint by seasoned, award-winning pros and we've been heads-down with the editing, sequencing, design, making physical dummies, as well as consolidating all written content. Hoping to finalize all content by May, going on press in July. We're planning the  official launch for end of September in NYC - stay tuned for more info.

Father Figure is also hitting the exhibition circuit - more news to come here as well.

Thanks for your love and support! The hard work continues...

name: Light, Shadows, Clouds and Cypress [EXPLORE]
description:
Walking in Valdorcia near San Quirico, typical tuscan landscape.

Passeggiando nei pressi di San Quirico d'Orcia, cipresso, nuvole, ombre e luci.. Toscana!!

I listened to "Lost for Words" at least 15 times today. My stomach pain is killing me... My heart hurts too because there is too much emotion stocked in my stomach and it pressures my heart.... It's my 31st birthday tomorrow and apparently my one and only wish is not going to come true... I am scared of tomorrow. All I need is a big hug.  It would be nice if we had those free hug guys in this city... but people are way to busy to give hugs... I have always wanted to die on my birthday to complete my cycle of life. Dying at the same day I was born at. I think it makes perfect sense. Otherwise, there'll be something missing... I don't know... I am talking about when I become really really old :) :) I hope there will be someone who knows me well enough to put some Pink Floyd instead of the Arabic prayers and stuff... OK enough of death... I walked under the sun today. That's a good sign...
